## Feature — activity-based lease renew + "about to be disconnected" warning modal

### Context

The DRAFT edit lease auto-renewed as long as the tab stayed **open**, regardless
of whether the user was actually doing anything: the client fired a blind
`setInterval` renew every ~TTL/3. So an editor who walked away (but left the tab
open) held the lock indefinitely and kept every other user read-only — the lease
only ever lapsed on a crashed/closed tab, never on a genuinely idle-but-open one.
Requested: tie renewal to real **activity** so an idle editor's lease lapses and
the next opener can reclaim it, and — before that happens — pop a **warning**
telling the user they are about to be disconnected from the project, with a
chance to stay. Frontend-only (plus doc/help-text touch-ups); no API or store
change.

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/global/js/edit-lock.js`
   - Renewal is now **activity-gated**: `mousemove` / `mousedown` / `keydown` /
     `wheel` / `touchstart` / `scroll` (capture phase) and tab re-focus stamp
     `lastActivityAt`. The keep-alive tick (`onRenewTick`, every ~TTL/3) only
     pings `/domain/edit-lock/renew` when the user has been active within the
     last renew interval — otherwise the lease ages and lapses for the next
     opener (matching the server-side reclaim).
   - New 1s **idle watcher** (`onIdleTick`) drives a warning **modal** built on
     the fly (`buildIdleModal`, static backdrop, Bootstrap `Modal` with a
     `notify()` fallback): when the remaining lease drops below `warnLeadMs`
     (≤60s, ≥10s, ≤TTL/3) it shows *"Still editing? …you will be disconnected
     from the project (read-only)"* with a live `M:SS` countdown and a **Keep
     editing** button. Acting (or clicking Keep editing) dismisses it and renews
     immediately; ignoring it until the countdown hits 0 flips to read-only and
     shows the existing "session expired" banner.
   - `remainingSeconds()` now derives from a shared `leaseRemainingMs()`; the
     navbar-badge tooltip copy updated to "renews while you work / released if
     you stay inactive". `stopRenew()` tears down the new timers, activity
     listeners, and the modal.
2. `src/back/objects/registry/lockmgt/EditLockService.py`
   - Module docstring lease paragraph updated: renews **while the editor is
     active**, and an idle editor (client stops renewing, warns first) is now an
     explicit cause of lease lapse alongside crash / closed tab.
3. `src/front/templates/partials/settings/_settings_locks.html`
   - Admin Locks help text notes a lock left by an **inactive** editor (warned
     first) is auto-reclaimed on lease lapse, alongside crashed/closed tabs.

### Modified files

- `src/front/static/global/js/edit-lock.js`
- `src/back/objects/registry/lockmgt/EditLockService.py`
- `src/front/templates/partials/settings/_settings_locks.html`

