## Fix: Settings → Locks showed a stale snapshot on re-entry

### Context

Opening Settings → Locks a second time (switch away and back, or return later)
kept showing the lock list from the *first* visit — you had to hit the Refresh
button to see the real current locks. The `sidebarSectionChanged` handler only
called `loadLocks()` on the first visit, guarded by a one-shot `locksLoaded`
flag; on re-entry the guard short-circuited, so the SPA-retained table was never
re-fetched. The Refresh button "worked" only because it reset `locksLoaded`.

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/config/js/settings-locks.js`
   - Removed the one-shot `locksLoaded` guard so `loadLocks()` runs every time
     the Locks section is (re-)opened — the table now always reflects the
     current locks. Simplified the Refresh and post-release handlers (no flag to
     reset) and dropped the now-dead `locksLoaded = true` in `loadLocks`. Updated
     the file header comment to describe the re-fetch-on-open behaviour.

### Modified files

- `src/front/static/config/js/settings-locks.js`

### Test result

- `node --check src/front/static/config/js/settings-locks.js` → clean.
- `uv run pytest -q -m "not scenario"` → **2971 passed, 275 skipped** (no test
