## Fix: OWL generator silently accepted token-truncated output (scenario 1)

### Context

Live scenario 1 intermittently timed out ("Wizard did not produce an ontology
within 420s") with **0 classes**. Root cause (from `logs/ontobricks.log`): the
generator's final Turtle answer hit the output-token cap, so `OntologyParser`
logged *"Content appeared truncated"* and `parse_rdf_flexible` failed for every
RDF syntax (turtle/xml/n3/nt/json-ld) → empty ontology. `agent_owl_generator`
called the endpoint with a fixed `max_tokens=4096` and, in the text-answer
branch, accepted the content **unconditionally** — it logged `finish_reason` but
never acted on `finish_reason == "length"`. A CRM/energy guideline (5 classes +
relationships + labels/comments), especially after a pitfall-fix round re-emits
the whole ontology, sits right at the 4096 boundary — hence the intermittency.

This is an LLM-agent change → handled under the AI-feature lifecycle gate
(`.cursor/12`), hotfix/regression tier: SPEC failure-mode + regression dataset +
unit coverage.

### Changes

1. `src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py`
   - Added `_GEN_MAX_TOKENS = 8192` (the documented endpoint output cap, matching
     `agent_auto_icon_assign._ABSOLUTE_MAX_TOKENS`) and used it at both
     `call_serving_endpoint` sites (was `4096`).
   - Added a **truncation guard** in the text-answer branch: when
     `finish_reason == "length"`, the cut-off Turtle is no longer accepted — the
     agent is asked to re-emit the complete ontology concisely (within
     `MAX_ITERATIONS`), or the run fails with an explicit "output truncated"
     error instead of landing a silent empty ontology.
2. `tests/units/agents/test_agent_owl_generator_truncation.py` (new)
   - Hermetic guard coverage (patched `call_serving_endpoint`): truncated→complete
     recovers; a truncated answer is never accepted verbatim; persistent
     truncation fails loudly.
3. `tests/eval/datasets/agent_owl_generator/regression.jsonl` (new)
   - The failing CRM/energy guideline captured as the regression case.
4. `.planning/agents/agent_owl_generator/SPEC.md`
   - Documented the truncation failure mode + mitigation; recorded the `8192`
     token budget in the identity table.

### Modified files

- `src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py`
- `tests/units/agents/test_agent_owl_generator_truncation.py` (new)
- `tests/eval/datasets/agent_owl_generator/regression.jsonl` (new)
- `.planning/agents/agent_owl_generator/SPEC.md`

### Test result

- `uv run pytest tests/units/agents/test_agent_owl_generator_truncation.py -q`
  → **3 passed**.
- Live re-validation (restart local app to load the new engine, then Ontology →
  Generate with the CRM/energy guideline / scenario 1) — pending.

## OWL generator: over-generation (class-explosion) guard

### Context

After the `8192` truncation fix, scenario 1 got *past* generation but failed at
**auto-map**: `Auto-Map produced no entity SQL within 600s`. Root cause was not
the mapper — it was genuinely working (`Chunk 9/22 done: +45 entities`) — but
the generator over-decomposed the ~5-entity CRM/energy guideline into **110
`owl:Class` declarations** (one class per column/value: `VatAmount`,
`MeterReading`, `Payment`, `Call`, …). The auto-mapper chunks ~5 classes/chunk
with cool-downs, so 110 classes → ~22 chunks → ~18 min, well past the scenario
`AUTOMAP_TIMEOUT`. The healthy baseline is ~10 classes / 4 chunks. The prompt
was the culprit: `GENERIC_GUIDELINES` authorised "30–60 classes" and the model
blew past even that.

This is an LLM-agent change → AI-feature lifecycle gate (`.cursor/12`),
hotfix/regression tier: prompt tightening + a deterministic, unit-testable
guard + SPEC failure-mode + regression dataset.

### Changes

1. `src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py`
   - Prompt: replaced the `GENERIC_GUIDELINES` "Size limits per iteration:
     30–60 classes" with "prefer the smallest set that covers the input
     (typically 8–25), one class per real-world entity, **never a class per
     column or attribute value** (those are datatype properties), hard limit
     40, consolidate rather than add".
   - Guard: added `_DEFAULT_MAX_CLASSES = 40`, `_MAX_CONSOLIDATE_ROUNDS = 2`,
     and `_count_owl_classes()` (regex over `a`/`rdf:type owl:Class`). In the
     text-answer branch, when the accepted Turtle exceeds `max_classes` the
     agent is asked (bounded by the round cap) to consolidate to the core
     entities before accepting; on exhaustion it accepts the best available
     ontology (no infinite loop). Overridable via `options["max_classes"]`
     (`<=0` disables).
2. `tests/units/agents/test_agent_owl_generator_class_cap.py` (new)
   - Hermetic guard coverage (patched `call_serving_endpoint`): count helper;
     over-cap→consolidated recovers; under-cap accepted directly; guard
     disabled via `max_classes=0`; persistent over-cap accepts best after the
     bounded rounds.
3. `tests/eval/datasets/agent_owl_generator/regression.jsonl`
   - Added `regression-crm-energy-overgeneration-002` (same CRM guideline,
     `max_classes: 40` constraint).
4. `.planning/agents/agent_owl_generator/SPEC.md`
   - Added the "Over-generation / class explosion" failure mode + mitigation
     and recorded `max_classes = 40` in the identity table.

### Modified files

- `src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py`
- `tests/units/agents/test_agent_owl_generator_class_cap.py` (new)
- `tests/eval/datasets/agent_owl_generator/regression.jsonl`
- `.planning/agents/agent_owl_generator/SPEC.md`

### Test result

- `uv run pytest tests/units/agents -q --no-cov` → **149 passed**
  (10 in the two owl-generator guard suites).
- Live re-validation (restart local app, re-run the scenario campaign) —
  pending.

